@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Terms";
}

<section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16">
    <div class="rounded-3xl border border-black/5 bg-white/80 p-10 md:p-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold">Terms of service</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm opacity-70">Last updated: @DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd")</p>
        <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-sm leading-6 opacity-80">
            <div>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Subscription and billing</h2>
                <p class="mt-2">Your agency subscribes to Traveleer on the plan selected during registration. Billing terms, user allowances, and trial availability follow the active plan attached to your workspace.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Use of the service</h2>
                <p class="mt-2">You are responsible for the supplier rates, quotes, client records, and booking content your team uploads. You must keep access credentials secure and use the platform lawfully.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Availability and change</h2>
                <p class="mt-2">We improve the product continuously. Features may evolve, but material changes that affect workflow or billing will be communicated clearly.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Cancellation and export</h2>
                <p class="mt-2">You can cancel according to your billing arrangement. Before closure, export any rate-card or quote data your team needs to retain.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Liability and governing law</h2>
                <p class="mt-2">The service is provided on a best-effort basis. To the extent permitted by law, liability is limited and indirect damages are excluded. Local governing-law treatment should be confirmed with your legal advisor before relying on this text as final counsel.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
